| Tool | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Java** | 21 | Core programming language |
| **Playwright** | 1.44.0 | Browser automation + Trace Viewer |
| **TestNG** | 7.11.0 | Test framework, listeners, parallel execution |
| **ExtentReports** | 5.1.2 | HTML report generation |
| **Apache Commons IO** | 2.15.1 | Screenshot file handling |
| **Maven** | — | Dependency management and build |

---

💡 Concepts Demonstrated

- **Trace Viewer** — `.zip` trace per test method, auto-opened on failure
- **`@BeforeMethod` / `@AfterMethod`** — trace lifecycle wraps each test
- **`setScreenshots(true)` + `setSnapshots(true)`** — full DOM + visual
  capture after every Playwright action
- **`ITestResult`** — TestNG result object used to detect failure and
  trigger viewer + screenshot
- **`ThreadLocal<BrowserContext>`** — context stored per thread so
  parallel runs each manage their own trace independently
- **Automatic Trace Viewer launch** — `ProcessBuilder` opens the viewer
  as a background process on failure without blocking the suite

---

🚀 How to Run

mvn exec:java -e -D exec.mainClass=com.microsoft.playwright.CLI -D exec.args="install"

mvn test

# Open any trace manually
mvn exec:java -e -D exec.mainClass=com.microsoft.playwright.CLI \
  -D exec.args="show-trace traces/chromium/testLogin.zip"
